message.content:
A king_snake is a non-venomous snake species known for its striking colors and patterns. 
They typically have a black base color with white or yellow bands that wrap around their body. 
Their skin has a smooth texture and their scales are tightly packed together. 
King_snakes are known for their slender, elongated body shape and their ability to climb trees. 
They can be found in various habitats such as forests, grasslands, and deserts. 
King_snakes are considered an important predator, feeding on rodents, lizards, and other snakes. 
They are also popular in the pet trade due to their striking appearance and docile temperament.
